@page "/support"

@* Static-SSR content page (no interactivity, no WASM) — mirrors SUPPORT.md so the
   blazordx.com/support link in FUNDING.yml and the license/docs resolves to a real page. *@

<PageTitle>Support — BlazorDX</PageTitle>

<section class="dx-section">
    <h1>Support</h1>
    <p class="dx-section-sub">
        BlazorDX is <strong>free and open source (MIT)</strong> — the whole library, forever.
        No license keys, nothing in the code gated behind a paid tier. The tiers below fund
        continued development and buy <em>people's time and guarantees</em>, not access to the code.
    </p>

    <p class="dx-demo-meta" style="margin-top:8px">
        ⚠️ Beta — built with substantial AI assistance and largely untested. Published for
        evaluation and testing only; not intended for production use.
    </p>

    <div class="dx-pillars">
        <div class="dx-pillar">
            <div class="dx-pillar-icon">💬</div>
            <h3>Community — free</h3>
            <p>The default for everyone.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Issues &amp; questions on the project repository.</li>
                <li>In-app docs (<a href="/docs">/docs</a>) and the repo guides.</li>
                <li>Best-effort; a minimal reproduction gets the fastest attention.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="dx-pillar">
            <div class="dx-pillar-icon">⏱️</div>
            <h3>Priority support — paid</h3>
            <p>For teams that need a dependable response.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Private channel with a target response time (e.g. 1–2 business days).</li>
                <li>Help with upgrades, integration, and configuration.</li>
                <li>Triage and prioritization of bugs that block you.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><a class="dx-btn-primary" href="mailto:support@blazordx.com?subject=BlazorDX%20priority%20support">Contact us</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="dx-pillar">
            <div class="dx-pillar-icon">🏢</div>
            <h3>Enterprise / SLA — paid</h3>
            <p>For production-critical adoption and procurement.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Contractual SLA on response and fix targets.</li>
                <li>Help passing your accessibility (WCAG/VPAT) and security reviews.</li>
                <li>IP indemnification and a signed support agreement.</li>
                <li>Roadmap influence and early access to releases.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><a class="dx-btn-primary" href="mailto:support@blazordx.com?subject=BlazorDX%20enterprise%20%2F%20SLA">Contact us</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="dx-pillar">
            <div class="dx-pillar-icon">🛠️</div>
            <h3>Custom development &amp; consulting</h3>
            <p>When you need more than the library ships with.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Bespoke components, theming, or integrations built to spec.</li>
                <li>Architecture review, training, and onboarding for your team.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><a class="dx-btn-primary" href="mailto:support@blazordx.com?subject=BlazorDX%20consulting">Contact us</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="dx-section">
    <h2>Sponsor the project</h2>
    <p class="dx-section-sub">
        BlazorDX stays MIT regardless of tier. Continued development and future advancements are
        funded through support contracts, sponsorships, and voluntary donations — none of which
        ever remove anything from the open-source library.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a class="dx-btn-primary" href="mailto:support@blazordx.com?subject=BlazorDX%20sponsorship">Sponsor or donate</a>
        <a class="dx-btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/logixrcorp/BlazorDX">View the source</a>
    </p>
</section>

<section class="dx-section">
    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p class="dx-section-sub">
        Found a vulnerability? Please report it privately to
        <a href="mailto:security@blazordx.com">security@blazordx.com</a> rather than opening a
        public issue. See the project's security policy for details.
    </p>
</section>
